SIMPLE: official
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Official
<hw>Of*fi"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>officialis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>officiel</ets>. See <er>Office</er>,
and cf. <er>Official</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to an office or public trust; <as>as, <ex>official</ex>
duties, or routine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That, in the <qex>official</qex> marks invested, you⟦br⟧
Anon do meet the senate.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Derived from the proper office or officer, or from
the proper authority; made or communicated by virtue of authority;
<as>as, an <ex>official</ex> statement or report</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>Approved by authority;
sanctioned by the pharmacopoeia; appointed to be used in medicine;
<as>as, an <ex>official</ex> drug or preparation</as>. Cf.
<er>Officinal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Discharging an office or function.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The stomach and other parts <qex>official</qex> unto
nutrition.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Official</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Official
<hw>Of*fi"cial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>officialis</ets> a
magistrate's servant or attendant: cf. F. <ets>official</ets>. See
<er>Official</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Officer</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who holds an office; esp., a subordinate executive
officer or attendant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ecclesiastical judge appointed by a bishop,
chapter, archdeacon, etc., with charge of the spiritual
jurisdiction.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>officialdom</ent>⟦br⟧
